      "Unlike centralized version control systems, Git is distributed, meaning every developer has a full copy of the project's history, improving resilience and enabling offline work.",
      "Git's data model uses content-addressable storage, where each file and directory is identified by a SHA-1 hash of its content, ensuring data integrity and preventing tampering.",
      "The popular web-based platform GitHub, founded in 2008, significantly contributed to Git's widespread adoption by providing a user-friendly interface and collaboration tools built on top of Git.",
      "As of 2023, Git is estimated to be used by over 90% of professional developers for version control, making it the dominant system in the software development industry."
